reviewText: I am a big fan of Gaffigan. This was good, but frankly not up to his usual excellent standard. Perhaps the food jokes are losing their appeal after so many years and variations?I hope he starts to stretch himself more.
Title: Jim Gaffigan: Obsessed

reviewText: Jim Gaffigan's Obsessed is yet another hilarious installment to his comedy repertoire.  His observational humor is on point with more jokes on food, family and more.  Highly recommended to anyone who has enjoyed his previous work.
summary: Jim Gaffigan Never Ceases to Entertain
Title: Jim Gaffigan: Obsessed

reviewText: Jim makes me cry with laughter once again! I first got into Jim Gaffigan when Mr. Universe came out (and then I sort of back-tracked and watched some of his older specials like "King Baby" and "Beyond that Pale" which were both hysterical) and I honestly couldn't enjoy his comedy more; everything is so relatable and all of his sets just glide into one another, like you're having a conversation with him.  This special was just as funny, if not funnier than Mr. Universe and I'd HIGHLY recommend buying! "Obsessed" is good clean fun for the whole family and will have you wondering why you didn't get into him before! Two thumbs way up!!!
Title: Jim Gaffigan: Obsessed

reviewText: Love Jim gaffigan!  This was for husband for fathers day.  Did NOT disappoint.  Saw him in San Diego, always been a big fan.  Great laughs!
Title: Jim Gaffigan: Obsessed

reviewText: I bought this DVD for my dad for Father's Day since he loves Jim Gaffigan.  I watched it with him and it was hilarious!  I laughed so hard my stomach hurt!  The best thing about it is that he's a very clean comedian.  It's nice, for a change, to watch a comedian who can be funny without being crass.
Title: Jim Gaffigan: Obsessed

reviewText: This is a poor follow up to his previous albums.  I did not hardly laugh at all. I am a big fan of his previous work but this is one to pass on.
